# []Dev Diaries] (https://tryhackme.com/room/devdiaries)
Hunt through online development traces to uncover what was left behind.

### Level: easy
### Tools Used:
- Any online subdomain finder
- Github
- git

1. `What is the subdomain where the development version of the website is hosted?` <br>
Search online for subdomain finder and paste in the website name. <br>
Ans: `uat-testing.marvenly.com`

2. `What is the GitHub username of the developer?` <br>
Scroll to the bottom of the website or the subdomain website. <br>
Ans: `notvibecoder23`

3. `What is the developer's email address?` <br>
For this we need to use our terminal. We need git installed. Then copy the github repo for the `marvenly_site` url from the dev's github. Then execute these commands to get the info about the dev and the project: <br>
`git clone https://github.com/notvibecoder23/marvenly_site` > `cd marvenly_site` > `git log`  <br>
We can see the info about the dev here. <br>
Ans: `freelancedevbycoder23@gmail.com`

4. `What reason did the developer mention in the commit history for removing the source code?` <br>
From the terminal we can see the reasons/Commits for each changes. <br>
Ans: `The project was marked as abandoned due to a payment dispute`

5. `What is the value of the hidden flag?` <br>
For this, just go to the github and look into the commit history. Then look through each commit changes. We find the flag in the second commit, `Removed my signature, ready for deployment`. <br>
Ans: `THM{g1t_h1st0ry_n3v3r_f0rg3ts}`

Done! Easy peesy.
